[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 2 406 905, with reports of cases by 214 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 96.3% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 31.7% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 165 153 deaths have been reported, 160 521 (97.2%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19; Spain is number 2 and Italy is number 3 followed by France, Germany, the UK, Turkey, Iran, and Russia as number 10. - Mod.MPP]

